Application programmin Interface

A--> api <--B

* communication btw two applications
* how the 2 applications can talk with each other (requests & responses)

    UI-->       api     <-- Backend
(Front end)                (Server side)

Types:
    1.Open APIs
    2.Partner APIs
    3.Internal APIs
    4.Composite APIs


Types of API architectures:
    1)REST-Representational State Transfer
    2)SOAP-Simple Object Access Protocol
    3)RPC-remote Procedural Call    

    Public API- publicily exposed and anyone with/without  credentials can use 
        *Google API
        *Twitter API

